Despite their large profits, the mining company has not mechanized the sulphur reduction to save costs, and does not provide any equipment to the carriers who work on their own account and are paid for by weight.
They also receive no part of the 30,000 rupees (2.5 euros) surcharge per camera, which the guards of this nature park, together with the entrance fee of 15,000 rupees (1.2 euros), demand from tourists who come to photograph the volcano and the human carrier.
