This made the series reach an audience record in that time.
When the answer became known in a chapter in November 1990, it was seen by an average of 41 million viewers turning the "Dallas" into the second most seen entertainment program since the end of "MASH" in 1983, which had 50 million viewers.
It was Kristin who had shot J.R.'s sister-in-law (interpreted by Mary Crosby).
